OL,3,CLow confidence in NHS complaints
OL,4,Cprocess 'stops patients flagging poor
OL,5,Ccare'
OL,7,FA lack of confidence in the NHS
OL,8,Fcomplaints process means some people
OL,9,Fare taking no action when they
OL,10,Fexperience poor care, according to the
OL,11,Fpatient champion.
OL,13,FThere is also "little evidence" that
OL,14,Fcomplaints being made to the health
OL,15,Fservice are being used to improve
OL,16,Fservices, Healthwatch England said.
OL,18,FIt comes as a poll showed more than
OL,19,Fhalf of those who made a complaint to
OL,20,Fan NHS organisation were not satisfied
OL,21,Fwith the process or outcome.
