OL,4,Cprocess 'stops patients flagging poor
OL,5,Ccare'
OL,7,FThe survey of 2,650 adults in England,
OL,8,Fcarried out by YouGov for Healthwatch,
OL,9,Ffound almost one in four (24%) had a
OL,10,Fpoor experience with the NHS in the
OL,11,Flast year.
OL,13,FHowever, 56% of these people took no
OL,14,Faction, with fewer than one in 10 (9%)
OL,15,Fmaking a formal complaint.
OL,17,FOf those who did not formally complain
OL,18,Fabout their experience, some 34% said
OL,19,Fit was because they did not think the
OL,20,Fhealth service would use the complaint
OL,21,Fto improve care.
