OL,7,FA third of people said they did not
OL,8,Fthink NHS organisations would respond
OL,9,Feffectively, while one in five said
OL,10,Fthey were worried that complaining
OL,11,Fwould affect their ongoing treatment.
OL,13,FSome 19% of those who experienced poor
OL,14,Fcare did not know how to complain, the
OL,15,Fpoll found.
OL,17,FOf those who did complain, some 56%
OL,18,Fwere dissatisfied with the process,
OL,19,Fwith the same proportion unhappy about
OL,20,Fthe outcome.
