OL,7,FFigures published in October show the
OL,8,Ftotal number of all reported written
OL,9,Fcomplaints in the NHS in 2023/24 was
OL,10,F241,922, an increase of 5.4% compared
OL,11,Fwith the 229,458 reported in the
OL,12,Fprevious 12 months.
OL,14,FHowever, the Healthwatch report claims
OL,15,F"low public confidence is preventing
OL,16,Fpeople from taking any action after
OL,17,Fexperiencing poor care", meaning that
OL,18,Fcurrent complaint numbers "could just
OL,19,Fbe the tip of the iceberg".
