OL,7,FIt added that "there is little
OL,8,Fevidence that complaints are being
OL,9,Fsystematically used to improve care".
OL,11,FAnalysis by Healthwatch shows there
OL,12,Fhas been a 37% hike in complaints
OL,13,Fbetween 2013/14 and 2023/24.
OL,15,FIt suggests this could mean people are
OL,16,Fmore confident about speaking up, as
OL,17,Fmore organisations adopt NHS
OL,18,FComplaints Standards which were
OL,19,Fintroduced in 2022.
