OL,7,FHowever, it also claims the rise could
OL,8,Fbe "driven by poorer quality of care
OL,9,Fcaused by pressures on the NHS,
OL,10,Fespecially since the pandemic".
OL,12,F"Despite year-on-year increases, the
OL,13,Fhealth service may not have learned
OL,14,Ffrom complaints and remains in a cycle
OL,15,Fof repeating the same mistakes," the
OL,16,Freport said.
OL,18,FMs Ansari added: "We flagged failings
OL,19,Fwith the NHS over a decade ago,
OL,20,Ffollowing the patient safety scandal
OL,21,Fat Mid Staffordshire Hospital.
